<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="70" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-08-18"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1484.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 2774, of the 10th ultimo, inclosing a copy of a note
                            addressed by you to the Tsung-li Yamên on that date, demanding that
                            viceroys, governors, and all other officials be held responsible by the
                            Chinese Government for antiforeign riots occurring within their
                            jurisdiction, and punished accordingly.</p>
                        <p>The Department approves generally the ground taken in your note to the
                            Tsung-li Yamên.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>